# Student Task Manager

A simple console-based Java project to manage student tasks efficiently.

## Overview

Student Task Manager is a menu-driven Java application that helps students organize their academic work.  
Users can add, view, update, delete, and mark tasks as completed using a simple console interface.

This project is built using core Java and demonstrates object-oriented programming concepts and CRUD operations.

## Features

- Add new tasks
- View all tasks
- Update existing tasks
- Delete tasks
- Mark tasks as completed
- Menu-driven console interface

## Technologies Used

- Java
- OOP (Object-Oriented Programming)
- ArrayList
- Scanner
- CRUD Operations

## Project Structure

StudentTaskManager/
└── src/
└── app/
├── Main.java
├── Task.java
└── TaskManager.java

## How to Run

1. Compile the project:

```bash
javac src\app\Task.java src\app\TaskManager.java src\app\Main.java
